<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101169339719680></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101169339719680><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101169339719680>lvling</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101169339719680#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=136898><span id=Scholar>Ceilironheart</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>23 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 22nd 5:57 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just wanted to share how I went from lvl 1 to 31 in 7 days and 12 hours of game time.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;     First off when you start kill the stuff outside of the gates of freeport until lvl 5. Then move to the next zone and kill things until lvl 7 from there get into a group and dont solo at all, I know some will say well you get more xps soloing and they are right, per kill they do get more xps but there downtime is alot more than someone in a group. So at lvl 7 i got into a orc group (camp 2) I made 10 got backstab and went to orc 1. Dont forget the belts you get dont sell them, some will say sell them for the plat but money comes with lvls not the other way around, so dont sell them. At lvl 11 or 12 go to orc highway in the OOM and remember group group group!! If youre not in a group that is going fast enough for you see who is in the zone and send them a tell to see if they have room for you, make sure its a tell because if you shout it the group youre in will get mad and prob boot you so make it in tells. Stay in oom until 17 and by then you should have atleast 150 plat auction to buy a stiletto of the bloodclaw its a great low to mid rogue weapon and they sell cheap I paid 100 plat for mine the proc is nice. At lvl 17 go to lake of ill omen if youre good go through FV and get the soulbinder to bind you in town, if evil go through overthere, bind there then run through Frontier Mtns into LOIO then either get a skelly group near the windmill or a frontdoor or backdoor group until 25. At 25 run to the Giant Fort in RM and hunt there. The reason you want to go to the giant fort is because the sarnaks are now blue to you so the xps arnt as great in a group and from 25 to 30 the giants are mostly red and the pulling is just as fast. The object is to always fight in a group that is a little higher than you so you will always be fighting reds and yellow. So at the 28-30 head over to the overthere and group up through 35. The loot sucks in the overthere it rly does but as i said before money comes with the lvls. ADD to note the reason you would go to the giant fort is also they drop some good selling items, i won a forest loop and sold it for 400 plat and bought some new armor when i got into the overthere, dont be afraid to send shouts out to people saying that yo need some better gear there is always A high lvl char out there that has some good equip in the bank that will sell it to you for cheap just to get rid of it. Hope this helps When I hit lvl 35 im going to DL and we'll see how that will go:) have fun and remember the view may not be the greatest from behind but youre not getting hit:)  <br>&nbsp;<br>Ceilironheart<br><br>44 rogue<br>19 sk<br>18 necro<br>17 druid<br>14 ranger<br>14 shammy<br>14 wizzy<br>5&nbsp;&nbsp;bard</td></tr>
