	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are welcome.<br><br>1. If you fail and the creature aggros and hits you then you are not hidden to anyone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Good luck and may the SOW be with you.  The skills Hide will stay greyed out until it recycles. Sneak does not get cancelled so if you need to run you need to turn Sneak off first.<br><br>2. Groups do not get pick pocket messages (oh, happy happy joy joy!).  But, some MOBs will scream &quot;Stop Thief!&quot; that everyone within talking range will hear, including your party.  Not all MOBs do.  Dervishes, NPCs, Gnolls, Bandits (pot calling the kettle black) will call out if you are detected.  Oddly enough Orcs won't.  You can't PP undead or animals so don't bother.  Giants don't call out - they just smush you.<br><br>3.  Until you get to be level 15 you actually can tank fairly well.  Go ahead and group. Other tank classes are only slightly better than you.  Until you get dual wield you should be using a shield anyway.  <br><br>4.  Unload the CB belts and get a dragoon dirk (30-40 pp). Since it is doubtful you will be fighting magic only creatures before level 12 a fine steel rapier or spear will do just dandy for now.  Those can be bought from other players for 10-15pp each.  Some people just give them away.<br><br>Slipskin Ashenheart<br>30 Rogue, Half Elf<br>Bertoxx Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
