<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101154297216572></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101154297216572><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101154297216572>RE: FP Rogue Guild</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101154297216572#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>292 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 20th 12:10 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You have to be really careful when going around the underground in Freeport. There are many evil trainers who are usually KOS to most rogues and can cast nasty spells on you. Fortuntely, none of them are anywhere near the rogue guild. My guess is that you're trying to get there the wrong way, through the abandoned building in East Freeport. The official EQ strategy guide claims it's the entrance to the rogue guild, but it's NOT. It does lead to the rogue guild, but you have to go through the nasty casters first. What you want to do instead is stay above ground and go to the seafarer's roost (by the docks). Instead of going in though, go down the nearby stairs to get underneath the docks. Then go through the door, down more stairs, and look for a false wall. If you look closely, there is a small round peep-hole in the false wall, or you can just run into all the walls until you walk through one. The rogue guild will be right there, with no casters nearby for miles. If that IS what you were doing, and you are still being attacked, then someone must have pulled a caster to the rogue guild. Wait a few hours and try again. Also, check to make sure your hide/sneak is working right. I've explored those caves while growing up 4 rogues, and I've never found anything down there that can see through hide. <br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 32nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Lords of Belterra<br>Xegony</td></tr>
