	   <tr><td colspan=2>The best way to manage your aggro is to always fight at max melee range from the mob. To do this back away from the mob until you see the message that you are too far away.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then take ONE step forward so that you can hit it.  A good way to gauge this is that pets always fight at max melee. If you do happen to get aggro, a quick evade is usually all you need. If that doesn't work, you need a new tank.<br><br>In some instances, Rogues can safely pull especially in zones like Dreadlands. You might take a couple of hits but you certainly won't die.<br><br>Sneak/hide is indeed a lifesaver. I have survived a couple of wipeouts in Hate by realizing things were going down and quickly ducking out of combat.  It makes the overall CR much much faster.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Dadiella 55th Lvl ROG Drinal<br><a href="http://www.unconquered.org" target=_new>http://www.unconquered.org</a><br></td></tr>
