	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey all! I'm back for a little while. Although I still haven't seriously played EQ in over 4 months now. Well anyway, when you switch to dual wield, a great choice for your offhand would be a dragoon dirk. It's a good price for your level (at most 50pp), although I'm not sure how much prices differ on PvP. Plus, dragoon dirk has a decent ratio for your level, and gives 3 vsMagic, to lessen your loss. When I think of magic resistance, a runed bone fork comes to mind. It gives +10 to magic, fire, AND cold resistances, and it fits in your range slot. However, the price runs anywhere from 500-800pp. There is something else you can use to help in duels against casters: Crystallized pumice, or just pumice stones. You can buy these from a couple vendors in Kelethin by the bank for about 20pp each. Each one holds 5 charges of nullify magic, which will cancel any root, snare, or DoT anyone tries to stick on you. Very useful, and imagine the caster's suprise when you start running at him after he rooted you:).<br><br>Edit: Oh one more thing. Some races get bonus resistances. I don't have the numbers in front of me, but I think halflings don't get any bonus, and dwarves get +5 in magic and poison. Heh, there's another argument for dwarves making the best rogues. ;)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan 16 09:20:02 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 32nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Lords of Belterra<br>Xegony</td></tr>
